PRIVACY POLICY
Updated 2022-08-23
In this privacy policy (The “Policy”) we at Kavalri Games AB, with the address Medborgarplatsen 25, 118 72 Stockholm, with the corporate company number 559164-5089 (herein “Kavalri Games”, “we”, or “us”), promise to take care of the personal information we collect from you. This includes information you provide us with, for example, when signing up on our website or opening an account connected to us or our products, as well as what we learn when you play our games. This Policy explains which personal information we collect from you and how we use and store such data, and how you can contact us about your data and invoke your rights.
We only collect, use, store and transfer (“process“) your personal information in accordance with applicable data protection legislation, including but not limited to the (EU) General Data Protection Regulation (2016/679) (“GDPR“) and applicable national data protection legislation (hereafter “applicable law“).
Depending on if you’re a website visitor, player or email subscriber, we will process personal information such as your contact details, your username, password(s) and payment details. We will also collect information about your technical equipment and devices such as hardware and software type, and other information you provide us with, for example when you sign up for our newsletter, surveys and forms.
We will use your personal information for different purposes. We will for example use the data to provide you with the service you have requested, such as accessing our game, and to improve our game and other services, to predict user trends, to make recommendations to you based on your usage, to process payments and customize our services to you.
We will engage other companies in order to fulfil our purposes and obligations as set out in this privacy policy, and we will transfer your personal information to countries that may not have as strict privacy legislation as where you live. We will only transfer your personal information to such countries if we are allowed to do so.
When we collect personal information from you, you are entitled to the following rights under applicable law:
The right to access and rectify your personal information
The right to object to our processing of personal information
The right to restrict to our processing of personal information
The right to demand us to delete your personal information
The right to data portability
If you have any questions or concerns regarding how we collect and use your personal information, please contact us:
info@kavalrigames.com
If you believe an infringement of your rights has occurred, you can lodge a complaint with the relevant data protection authority.
You can also contact us via mail:
