CONTENT
1. Us, Kavalri Games
We are Kavalri Games (“Kavalri Games”, “us”, “we”, “the company”). This privacy policy applies to the websites operated by us including kavalrigames.com and equestrianthegame.com
The Policy also applies to your use of our services such as communication platforms and when you play our games (all of the above called “Services”).
We are the controller of the personal information collected. If you have any questions or want to know more about how we use your personal information, please contact us via email
info@kavalrigames.com
or via mail to the address stated above.
2. Our undertaking
We promise to not sell your data to third parties and to take measures to keep your information and data safe. You have the right to access and delete your data as well as review marketing choices and other information, such as newsletters, you get from us.
3. Personal information
Personal information is any information relating to an identified natural person. It can be information that could allow us to identify you both directly and indirectly (for example your name, email address, IP address, billing address). In this Policy, we use the word “data” to refer to personal information.
4. Reasons for processing your data
We will only use and process data about you if we have one of these reasons to do so:
To fulfil a contract with you (for example a purchase of our services).
When it’s our legal duty (for example to make sure we are not collecting data from children, for bookkeeping purposes and to fulfil obligations in relation to authorities).
When you consent to it (for example when subscribing to our emailing list).
When it is in our legitimate interest (for example to enforce our policies, manage our everyday business, to use in an anonymized and aggregated way in order to perform statistical analysis, for marketing purposes, to ensure information security or to transfer data within the organization).
5. When we collect your data
We will collect your data when you use our Services, including: signing up to our emailing list, playing our games, taking forms and surveys from us, using our websites, participating in playtests, taking part in competitions and events.
6. The data we collect
We collect data that you explicitly provided to us in different situations. We also collect information generated by your device.
Data that you explicitly provide us with can for example be:
email address, username, country, age, name, password(s) created to access parts of our Services, nicknames.
When making a purchase of our Services, you may have to provide us with your physical address, telephone number, card information and payment account details, PayPal account details.
As well as any other data that you provide us with when you contact us via email, fill out surveys or forms, enter contests or apply for a job at the Company.
Data we collect when you use our Services:
Profile and user data. Including the profile you create to identify yourself when you use our Services and internet protocol (IP) address and cookies that may uniquely identify your browser. It also includes other data about how you use our Services. We gather this data from devices you use to connect to these Services, such as computers and mobile phones, using cookies and other internet tracking software.
Payment and transaction data
Location data
Platform type
Preferred language
Gender
Information about your device
Referral pages and page exit time
Advertiser ID or other platform IDs
In-game activity including, but not limited to, what games you play, own, how you play, how often and for how long
Game crash reports and error dump information from your device
Multiplayer sessions, when these sessions were played and which players were in them
Friend relations added to friend lists in games
7. How we use your data
We use the information that we collect from you and your use of our Services in order to provide, maintain, protect and improve our services and develop new services. Unless you opt out, we will use the information to offer you tailored content such as more relevant advertisements and inform you about releases and news which you might be interested in.
We will not use your data for any other purpose than for which the data was originally collected.
In order to improve your gaming experience and operate our business, we use the information collected from you:
To operate, improve, develop and provide you with our Services
To give you recommendations and offers
To respond to inquiries from you
To verify your identity in order to prevent unauthorized access
To provide you with software updates
To understand trends in usage
To calculate advertising performance
To help tracking and correcting errors and bugs in games and services
To customize your user experience
To maintain the integrity and security of the Services
To process transactions and communicate with you regarding these transactions
To administer and perform play- and beta tests which you have signed up for
To create reports, analyses or similar for the purpose of research and business intelligence and be able to track potential problems, behaviour and trends
To enforce our terms of conditions and this Policy
To send you newsletters and promotional notices and offers you have previously agreed to
To keep our Services fair, investigate and prevent fraud and illegal behaviour
To comply with applicable laws and regulations
You can at any time object to our use of your personal information for marketing purposes, and we will then stop using your personal information for such purposes.
8. Who we share your information with
To be able to provide you with the best possible experience of our Services, we may share your data with other companies and organizations. We may share your information with following partners:
Game distribution platforms (for example Steam)
Co-publishing partners
Market research agencies
Payment providers (for example PayPal)
Companies that help support our services (for example Braincloud, Facebook)
Advertising partners (for example Google, Facebook)
For Unity games, Unity is our service provider and may collect data in relation to your use of such services. Unity’s privacy policy:
https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
Our games use Google as an analytics service provider. Google’s privacy policy can be found here: https://policies.google.com/privacy
We may release your data when we are required to by a court order, according to law or in the event of a bankruptcy or other similar event.
We may also share and may acquire your data with future subsidiaries or companies if we choose to sell, transfer or merge parts of our business.
9. Are children allowed to use our services?
Our services are not directed towards children and we do not knowingly collect information from children under 13 years of age. Only children over 13 may create an account in order to engage with services such as our communication platform(s).
If we obtain actual knowledge that we have collected data from a child under 13 years of age, we will delete it unless we are legally obligated to retain that data.
10. Cookies and tracking technologies
We may use cookies and pixel tags to collect information about visitors on our websites. Cookies allow us to recognize your computer while you are on the website and customize your experience. Please note that you can choose to disable cookies on most web browsers.
11. Security measures
We maintain safeguards to help keep your data secure. We restrict access to your data only to those persons who have a legitimate purpose to access it. We encourage you to be careful when sharing your data with other users or when using Services like forums or chat.
We will never ask for your password to be sent to us.
12. Choosing not to share your data with us
If you choose not to share your personal data, it may prevent us from providing you with our Services. It may also mean that we have to cancel a product or Service you have with us and that you will be unable to play certain parts of our games.
13. How long do we keep your data?
We keep your information for as long as you are a customer. We may keep the information for longer for research purposes. If we do, we will make sure the information is anonymised and non-traceable to you as a person.
We will also keep the data longer if we are required to for legal reasons. We will delete data that is no longer necessary after a reasonable period. We will also delete your data upon request.
14. Accessing, changing and updating your data
You have the right to access the data relating to you. You have the right to rectify or add data if the information is inaccurate or incomplete. As soon as we become aware of any inaccurate personal information being processed, we will rectify your data without undue delay.
15. Right to object to the processing of your data
You have the right to object to the processing of your data. As we must process some information in order to provide you with the Services, you cannot object to all our use of personal information and still require us to provide Services to you.
You may unsubscribe at any time from newsletters you previously opted-in to by following instructions in the newsletter sent to you.
16. Right to erasure
You have the right to request that we erase the data related to you.
17. Right to restriction
You are entitled to require us to restrict our processing of your personal information if you contest the accuracy of the data, if the processing is unlawful but you do still not want us to erase the data, if the data is no longer needed to fulfil the purpose it was collected for or you have informed us that you do not consider us to have a legitimate interest for certain processing.
18. Enforcing your rights
You can contact us via email at any time in order to get the data we have collected from you or get such data deleted or invoke other rights explained above. Please note we will not delete any data if we are unable to verify that you are their rightful owner.
19. Changes to the privacy policy
This Policy may change from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page.
